column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny to partly cloudy- light NW wind- boating activity. 0.4" of rain yesterday.
Sunny- light SW wind- no recent rain- substantial boating activity
Sunny- light SE wind.  Lake quiet with calm spots- little boating activity- last rain sun. 6/4 (~.6") .
Mostly sunny- but a storm is moving in from the east-east wind light- little boating activity- lake level back to normal- last rain Thursday a.m.
Hazy sun- light NW wind- little boating activity- slight algae bloom started- last rain Monday 7/25-water temp. 75 degrees.
Partly cloudy- light SW wind- little boating activity- last rain 8/7/94- water temp. 72 degrees.
Partly cloudy- SW wind- lake level normal- no rain of significance for 1 week- no algal bloom.
Sunny- light S wind- some green algae on water surface early a.m. last rain on Sunday night 6/30-water temp. 70s. some boating- water and jet ski activity.

Partly cloudy to mostly sunny.  Light SW breeze- no visible algae bloom- water temperature 75 degrees- last rain wed pm 8/7 and early Thursday am 8/8 (heavy with high winds-heavy tree damage in three lakes area) .

Mostly sunny to partly cloudy- light NE breeze- no rain since sun. 8/25- air temps daytime 70's night cooling to 40's. water temp. 70 degrees- lake quiet- no water-skiing or jet skis since weekend- few boaters.
Partly sunny- winds 10 miles per hour- air temperature 73 degrees.
Mostly cloudy- wind 11 mph from southwest- minimal boat traffic. Birds and bald eagle flying overhead.
Mostly sunny- few clouds- wind NNW 7-8 mph- minimal boat activity.
Sunny- few clouds/haze- wind SSW 11mph- a lot of boat traffic on lake this holiday weekend.
Sunny- few clouds- wind SSE 12 mph- no boat traffic- air temp 72 degrees.
Cloudy/Partly sunny; wind NW 8 mph; no boat traffic; air temp 65 degrees; Water surface temp 72.5 degrees; humidity 75%
Sunny- air temp 75 degrees- wind 1-2 mph- no boat traffic.
Sunny and no clouds; air temp 68 degrees; wind 8 mph from the south; no real boat traffic - 1 fisherman and 1 sailboat
Sunny with a few clouds; air temp 70 degrees; wind 8 mph out of southeast; 3 fisherman; water is cloudy and looks like fall turnover is beginning.
Partly cloudy; 66 degrees F; wind 11 - 15mph out of NNW; minor boat activity

Air temperature 66 degrees; cloudy with a little sun peeking out; wind 7 mph out of the ESE; no boat activity. Air temperature 66 degrees; cloudy with a little sun peeking out; wind 7 mph out of the ESE; no boat activity.

Sunny- only a few clouds. 77 degrees F; wind 4 mph out of SSW; minor boat activity. Noticed a green film on Lake surface in the morning - could be a start to the Fall turnover given cooler night time temps.
Sunny- no clouds. Air temp - 81 degrees. Water surface temp 72.4 degrees. Wind calm/1 mph out of the south; minor boat activity.  Turnover in process.
